HEADWORD: Darksome
<hw>Dark"some</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Dark; gloomy;
obscure; shaded; cheerless.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He brought him through a <qex>darksome</qex> narrow pass⟦br⟧
To a broad gate, all built of beaten gold.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>darky</ent>⟦br⟧
